column11: APPROX. 5-6" ABOVE NORMAL-STAFF GAUGE NOT IN
2" ABOVE NORMAL. A LOT OF RAIN.

Migrated from EPA STORET Legacy Database- originally reported by Wisconsin DNR
Overcast- calm- heavy rain 2 days ago
Clear- heavy waves- 2 days after heavy rain
Mostly sunny- mod. waves- 2 days after heavy storm
Sunny- few clouds- 2 days after 1st snow- loon still here
Clear- calm- beautiful- lake froze totally 11/12- then thawed- last reading
Clear- wavy- water dark and cloudy- ice out: 4/18.  Water level: up 3"
Cloudy- water improving.  Water level: up 2"
Algae bloom: 5/13- lake level down due to beaver dam removal
Shoreline murky- 2 days heavy rain- cloudy- wavy- beaver dam repaired
Sunny- wavy- shoreline murky.  Water level: Up .5"
Sunny- moderate waves- water quality decreasing
Cloudy- moderate waves- heavy rain the last 2 days.  Water level up 1"
Cloudy- calm- heavy rain for 2 days
Clear- bright- moderate waves- water temp: 76 F
Clear- moderate waves- cloudy- green matted masses floating
Beautiful day- water calm and very cloudy
Water calm and cloudy-- worse close to shore- water level holding.
Overcast- heavy waves.  Water level: Up 1.5"
Overcast- slight waves- heavy rain the day before
Cloudy- slight ripples- 38 F- first snow 10/15 (measurable) - first snow 9/19.  Water level: up 2"
Sunny- warm- slight waves.  Water level: Up 2.5"
Beautiful- sunny day- water calm and clear.  Water level: Up .5"
Overcast- light waves.  Water level: Up .5"
Sunny day- lake is calm- water clear but gobs of green slime on bottom around the shoreline.  Saw 1 osprey- blue heron- and a loon.
Sunny- calm- water clear but bottom is green.  Water level: Up .5"
Partly sunny- slight waves- observed 3 eagles- 1 adult and 2 young.  Water level: up 2"
Overcast- lake is calm- light rain for the last 2 days.  Water level: Up .5"
Completely overcast- rain and more to come. Water level up 1"
Slight waves- a few minutes of sunshine- and then overcast again more rain to come. Water level up 1"
Sunny- very slight waves- took the boat out one more time after 5" of snow...have a nice winter.
One day after ice out- cold- rain- overcast- slight waves- water dark brown- loons are here!
Clear day- moderate waves- dam opened- water level dropping.
After heavy rain- dam opened- lowering lake level- light waves
Overcast- lake calm- water level dropped 4" since last reading
Some clouds- slight waves.  Water level: up 1" above normal
Few clouds- nice day- heavy rain yesterday.  Temperature is dropping.
Nice day- after days of having slight waves.
Lake level high after heavy rain- beautiful day- slight waves.
Clear day- moderate waves- first snow on the ground- Sept. 29.  Water level: up 3"
Overcast- lake is calm- water is nice and clear.
Beautiful day- sunny- slight waves- water is clear- clear- best all year.  This will be the last report this year- deep snow.
Ice out 4/19/94- overcast- water calm- first loon 4/20.
Lake level went down to 4" below normal- then up again to 3" below after heavy rain + snow.  Partly cloudy light waves.  Beaver dam has been opened.
Beautiful day- water very clear- slight waves.
Overcast- slight waves- looks like rain- dam opened.
Clear day- slight waves- water level very low- beaver dam has been opened-torn down.
Clear sky- lake calm- water very clear- have never seen it like this in 11 years.
Cloudy- light waves- lake level up after 2 days of rain.
Cloudy- lake level almost normal after days of rain.
Overcast- lake level back to normal- slight waves.
Hot- overcast- lake calm- rain night before.
Partly cloudy- first day no rain- slight waves.
Cloudy- a few short showers in the morning- slight waves.
Overcast- slight waves- water very clear.
Clear nice day- lake calm- water level down- lots of weeds.
Rain for 2 days- more on the way.  Total overcast.  Lake level up.
Dam opened.  Beautiful clear day after days of rain.  Water not as clear- I assume due to construction on beaver river culvert.
Beautiful clear day- slight waves- temp. down to 40 degrees.
Clear day- slight waves- soon last boat has to come out.  Will test as late as possible.
Public perception due to cloudy brown color.  Water very cloudy- beautiful day- lake calm.
Overcast- slight waves- 1 loon- 2 bald eagles.
Partly cloudy- moderate waves- water temp. 62 degrees.
Sunny- no waves- 1 eagle- 1 osprey- 1 loon.  This is my 100th secchi dip since July 11th- 1990.
Hot 94 degrees- water temp. 79 degrees.  Lake very still- water beautiful.
Partly cloudy- rain on and off- slight waves- 7 days of rain and more on the way.
Overcast- ripples- 3 loons on lake- 1 eagle.
Overcast- lake calm- sorry missed last reading- went on vacation.
Overcast- lake calm- temp. drop to 57 degrees-water temp 70 degrees.
Few clouds- slight waves- water temp. 74 degrees.
Sunny- lakes calm.  Also did test on 2 connecting lakes.  McCullough 7' green.  Beaver 4.5' brown.
Overcast-moderate waves-rain for days-lake level up.
Public perception due to floating cottonwood bloom.
The first beautiful clear day in a week.
Public perception due to cloudy water. First clear day after many days of rain. Slight ripples. Loon baby hatched on connecting Lake McCullough- 1 baby.
Water very cloudy.  Clear day after many days of rain.
Rain almost every day.  On the way 1 eagle- 2 loons- one muskrat.
Algae bloom.  Beautiful clear day- lake calm.
Muddy- overcast- lake calm. McCullough Lake connecting to Morton is also very muddy. 4'.
Loons still here. Overcast. Rain on and off all day. Lake calm. Connecting lakes McCullough 4.5'. Beaver lake 4.5'.
Beautiful day- water has cleared up nicely. 1 loon still here.
Beautiful day. Loons nesting. Blue heron and eagles are here.
Also checked secchi for Beaver Lake - 2960600 = 5 feet. and McCullough #2960400 = 7.50 feet.
Overcast. Slight waves.  One loon and chick.
Partly cloudy. Lake calm. Water very clear. McCallough Lake #2960400 = 9 feet.
Water still beautiful after heavy traffic.  Few clouds. Slight ripples. 3 loons and 1 eagle.
Also checked secchi for Beaver Lake - 2960600 = 6 feet. and McCullough #2960400 = 7.75 feet.
Partly cloudy.  Moderate waves.  Temperature 72 degrees.
Cloudy with slight waves on the water.
Clear beautiful.  1 egg in loon nest.
Few clouds slight waves.  1 baby loon.
Few clouds moderate waves.  Beautiful day.  1 egg on loons nest not hatched.
Beautiful day- temp 80 deg- 2 loons- 3 otters- water calm- ice out 4/15.
Partly cloudy- slight waves- 2 loons- 1 kingfisher.
Water level high after heavy rain- Great American Secchi Dip In 7/2/99: 7.5 feet.
4 loons- also took reading in McCullough (7 ft) and Beaver Lake (3 ft).
Sunny- beautiful day- 2 eagles- hummingbirds gone.
Beautiful- few clouds- two loons- and one eagle.
Beautiful- sunny- and some algae.  McCullough Lake 9 Ft and Beaver Lake 6 Ft- connecting lakes.
Overcast- two loons- three otters- and one kingfisher.
(Satellite date).  Overcast- two loons- and one kingfisher.
Partly cloudy- slight waves- and two loons.
Cloudy.  Could not make it on the 4th satellite date.
Total overcast- two loons- on blue heron- and one osprey.
Water is very low- went down 12" in five days.  McCullough 5 Ft and beaver 3 Ft for the secchi depth.
Water level is very low. Beaver dam taken out- weeds.
Not able to keep satellite date (8-21).  Water level very low.  Lots of weeds.
Beautiful day.  Slight waves- water level very low.
Clear day- water choppy. 2 loons with chick.
Clear- sunny- very cold. 1 foot snow over the weekend. this is the last reading for this year.
The water is choppy- overcast- ice out on April 22- and loons are here.
Sunny- clear- one eagle- two loons- and slight waves on the water.
Partly cloudy- water very low- two loons- and one blue heron.
The water is very low- beaver dam destroyed- few clouds- and two loons.
The air temperature is 87 degrees- water temperature is 79 degrees- light waves- overcast- and two loons.
Slightly overcast but sunny- two loons- one eagle- and the water is very low.
Could not keep satellite date- but try to do as close as possible.
Water very low- 1.5ft below normal- and two loons but no chicks.
Total overcast- water lowest ever- blue heron- and a beaver.
Sunny with few clouds- two mature loons and two young- and one blue heron.
Sunny- three loons - one adult and two young- and a beaver.
Overcast and ripples on the lake.  This is the last entry- boat had to come out because of low water- one shoreline.
Very warm- breezy- saw loon diving.
Warm- sunny- calm- prior weeks heavy rains.
I give up. I put my boat away for the winter- but I will certainly do this again next year. Send me a notice as when to start
cool night in mid 50's four days in a row.
cloudy and windy clear and windy
